The paper discusses a neural network-based approach for question answering, which is a common topic in the fields of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on a sequence labeling model for open domain factoid question answering, which suggests a focus on NLP and information retrieval (IR) techniques. The paper also mentions challenges related to softmax computation and candidate answer generation, which are common issues in the fields of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning. Finally, the paper proposes a new dataset for evaluating the proposed model, which suggests a focus on data-driven approaches and machine learning. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
